goals.question: What is the distribution of node sizes in the hierarchy?
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the range of node sizes and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the most common parent node in the hierarchy?
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the most common parent node and understand the hierarchy structure.

goals.question: What is the distribution of node names in the hierarchy?
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the most common node names and understand the hierarchy structure.

goals.question: What is the relationship between node size and parent node?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of size and parent fields
goals.rationale: This helps to identify any patterns or correlations between node size and parent node.

goals.question: What is the distribution of node identifiers in the hierarchy?
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the range of node identifiers and identify any gaps or missing nodes in the hierarchy.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node sizes in the hierarchy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='parent', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the most common parent node in the hierarchy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    sns.countplot(y="name", data=data, order=data['name'].value_counts().iloc[:20].index)
    plt.xlabel("Count")
    plt.ylabel("Node Name")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of node names in the hierarchy?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
